In [2]:
def plot_graph(G):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
    pos=nx.spring_layout(G)
    nx.draw(G, with_labels = True, pos = pos)
    plt.show(True)

def read_graph(filepath):
    G= nx.read_edgelist(filepath, nodetype=int, comments='%') # Read the network
    Gcc=sorted(nx.connected_component_subgraphs(G), key = len, reverse=True)
    G=Gcc[0]
    G = nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers(G, first_label=0)
    N = len(G)
    M = G.number_of_edges()
    print('Number of nodes:', N)
    print('Number of edges:', M)
    return G

def read_gml_graph(filepath):
    M= nx.read_gml(filepath) # Read the network
    G = nx.Graph()
    for u,v,data in M.edges(data=True):
        w = data['weight'] if 'weight' in data else 1.0
        if G.has_edge(u,v):
            G[u][v]['weight'] += w
        else:
            G.add_edge(u, v, weight=w)
    Gcc=sorted(nx.connected_component_subgraphs(G), key = len, reverse=True)
    G=Gcc[0]
    G = nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers(G, first_label=0)
    N = len(G)
    M = G.number_of_edges()
    print('Number of nodes:', N)
    print('Number of edges:', M)
    return G

def read_digraph(filepath):
    G= nx.read_edgelist(filepath, create_using=nx.DiGraph, nodetype=int, comments='%') # Read the network
    Gcc=sorted(nx.connected_component_subgraphs(G), key = len, reverse=True)
    G=Gcc[0]
    G = nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers(G, first_label=0)
    N = len(G)
    M = G.number_of_edges()
    print('Number of nodes:', N)
    print('Number of edges:', M)
    return G

def read_graph_weighted(filepath):
    G= nx.read_edgelist(filepath, nodetype=int, data=(('weight',float),), comments='%') # Read the network
    Gcc=sorted(nx.connected_component_subgraphs(G), key = len, reverse=True)
    G=Gcc[0]
    G = nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers(G, first_label=0)
    N = len(G)
    M = G.number_of_edges()
    print('Number of nodes:', N)
    print('Number of edges:', M)
    return G

Some useful functions¶

In [36]:
def avg_neighbor_degree_network(G):
    knn = []
    for i in G.nodes():
        aux =  nx.average_neighbor_degree(G, nodes = [i])
        knn.append(float(aux[i]))
    knn = np.array(knn)
    print("Average degree of the neighborhood of the network:", np.mean(knn))
    return knn

def plot_k_knn(G, knn):
    vk = dict(G.degree())
    vk = list(vk.values())
    knnk = list()
    ks = list()
    for k in range(np.min(vk), np.max(vk)):
        aux = vk = k
        if(knn[aux] > 0):
            av_knn = np.mean(knn[aux]) #average clustering among all the nodes with degree k
            knnk.append(av_knn)
            ks.append(k)
    plt.plot(ks, knnk, 'ro')
    plt.ylabel("knn(k)")
    plt.xlabel("k")
    plt.grid(True)

    # determine best fit line
    par = np.polyfit(ks, knnk, 1, full=True)
    slope=par[0][0]
    intercept=par[0][1]
    xl = [min(ks), max(ks)]
    yl = [slope*xx + intercept  for xx in xl]
    plt.plot(xl, yl, '-b')
    plt.show(True)
    return ks, knnk
